data.description: Talk about Peace and quiet!  Stars seem so close you could reach up and touch them. Country living at its' finest with Plenty of wild life! This area of Escambia county offers a more country style of life as you will find horses, cows, chickens, homes on larger parcels of land and a lot of planted fields! ***$5,000 Buyer Closing cost/Buy Down Allowance with acceptable offer**** This main house has a 3 bedroom & 2 baths with brick siding and separate mother in law /apartment. MIL/APT has 1 bedroom, 1 bath, full kitchen and living/dining combo with a large breezeway/covered patio area. Property also offers an oversized one car garage with attic storage and 5 covered parking places. Mostly fenced yard surrounding 3.62 acres.  Two Plum trees, 2 Pecan Trees, 1 Lemon tree, 1 peach tree. The lemon, peach and 1 plum are producing. Roof replaced in 2023,Septic last pumped 4/2019, Water Heater replaced 4/2015, Hvac replaced 2015. Fresh paint , new carpet in guest bedrooms, new floor in guest bath. Smooth ceilings in main living area , wood burning fire place,  Pantry, coat and linen closets. There is a yard building with shelving approx 16x12 ,The 2 stall barn with tack room will convey "as-is", needs some TLC! Plenty of room to add a new home or a pool! Zoned Rural Residential so bring your horses.  As per Escambia County Planning and  Zoning up to 4 horses allowed. You will LOVE this place!
